  "prompt": "What is the main function of the brachiocephalic artery?",
  "response": "The main function of the brachiocephalic artery is to supply blood to the upper limbs and the head and neck. It is a major artery that originates from the aortic arch and branches into the right common carotid artery and the right subclavian artery. The right common carotid artery delivers oxygenated blood to the right side of the head and neck, while the right subclavian artery supplies blood to the right arm. In essence, the brachiocephalic artery plays a crucial role in the circulation system by ensuring that these regions receive adequate blood supply.",
